[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating native image metadata**\n\nI'm reflecting on native image metadata and how it connects with lambda functions. During a JVM test, the agent is noticing specific lambda classes and the readResolve function of SerializedLambda. I wonder if this might lead to some configuration generation? It seems that when a native image is compiled, the lambda class names can differ from what they are in the JVM. I think I'm curious about those hidden lambda proxy names too!\n\n**Considering SerializedLambda**\n\nI need to ensure ClosureSerializer is functioning properly, but constructing a SerializedLambda is also necessary. I'm wondering if this is a requirement of the public API, given it uses a public constructor without reflection. Testing a fake lambda might be less straightforward, and perhaps readResolve will validate certain aspects? The JDK SerializedLambda.readResolve implementation inspects the class and invokes a method. Our method could simply return a new Operation, thus covering the readResolve requirement effectively.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0f11957e5262e9c20169f27f35158081a3aed172ab9a099f73\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp8n9L6-H9RWO4SWegyqdPvlmYP12Kld06QhnaL0gPCdHwXl8zW2me39Jpv53cImmLA1keyq5gd_sCSZdLvgvrabK8nZjccILI1CsWmm9CmMs8e113vsvvELBJpor1oytsbvx4UAMOdNxT71zHoFCL6zNaPlxo1IjF5N-FWnfN8oJlMID9FweoVGyGzIrLl5nJFEiQK9AyarpKPbzutHWJzuaBCDybPs_25OioVio26R1zyZ9Syw8MQfohqpzVaFMvSrz1oJ3Q7atgo0Zh6WNUR02YzJNF6gUPlXDcRP6PFd4Fqo2e6tFPMGowYQwxBuJDbtcPBmuv15nnN88StuSW-G75SASfhZSPb7xmm8WFfnJYNQXHIsVYCfxOqHm-AB2mI9A9_aJBrRQkSSYe9HK5qnCt_PWzzrNn8kc7EyKQsE8c4zNmjINQ7vOMzzncDLswYuXeRpYS7pQEMuRmXJrD5MO8lWqx9yYobeP8T1LbSGIac2TsW1-VOykF3niV4oBprXDgRyuT_XeCOdO1p8VCWu4VdlE1UCwqB2m-CcMfVNlrDg_x24qE0mqgXPnHedSwSitFmeqfTE4JbqpFJcfGb-dsASyfF_BraaoGKbVTrLwAeXRXN2MKX_u-UEafVrCtj4fHAB_gErQsV2N46OW-v724wTojeSxS-AYwIsOkEGI1ihyABlUJTt5x6BSsuZ